TB’s options:
Pats: but possibly without Josh and a weak draft. Maybe strong free agent pickups for the offense like they did in 2007. Too many maybes
Definite and established teams below:
A grade: Cowboys good RB and Receivers. Jerry Jones would definitely draft to support Brady if he thinks Brady gives him a chance to win a SB. Best offensive line of the three.
B grade: Brady and Josh A grade Cleveland two good RBs, receivers, and TE
B grade: Don’t really like the receivers but their big targets. Chargers two good RBs, receivers, and TE. Chargers will need to keep Gordon
All teams with quality defense
Titans: if they don’t resign Tannehill this fit might work. Has a History wit coach, good RB. Young rising receivers. Good defense. I think would draft to support Brady.

Josh could possibly bring Brady wit him if he leaves, which could help the development of a young QB to be mentored by Brady. If a young QB has the humility to step down and be mentored.

Just my thoughts.
